appearances were covered by media ranging from postcards to radio broadcasts. Worship of the emperor through viewing his image, Hori shows, taught the Japanese people how to look at images and primed their enjoyment of early animation and documentary films alike. Promiscuous Media links the political and the cultural closely in a way that illuminates the nature of twentieth-century Japanese society.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aJapan-History-1926-1945. 0aMass media and nationalismzJapanxHistoryy20th century. 0aMass media and nationalism-Japan-History-20th century. 0aMotion picturesxPolitical aspectszJapanxHistoryy20th century. 0aMotion pictureszJapanxHistoryy20th century. 0aMotion pictures-Japan-History-20th century. 0aMotion pictures-Political aspects-Japan-History-20th century. 0aNationalism and the artszJapanxHistoryy20th century. 0aNationalism and the arts-Japan-History-20th century. 4aAsian Studies. 4aFilm. 4aHistory. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / History & Criticism.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAsian Studies Contemporary Collection eBook Packagez978311064982608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311066587108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts 2018z9783110603088oZDB-23-DPK08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts, Architecture and Design 2018 Englishz978311060397208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018 Englishz978311060425208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018z9783110603255oZDB-23-DGG40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781501709524zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501709524423Coveruhttps:/